This means the equation $x^2 + r = x \sqrt{3},$ or $x^2 - x \sqrt{3} + r = 0$ will have exactly one solution.
Hence, the discriminant will be 0, so $3 - 4r = 0,$ or $r = \boxed{\frac{3}{4}}.$

